color:black&quot;&gt;At the time of the food hygiene inspection a new state of the art, detailed cleaning process had recently been introduced in the production unit. This process requires a large volume of water. Due to the amount of water used, pipe work was found to be leaking in a non-food room below the food production unit.&amp;nbsp; As soon as this matter was brought to the attention of the Senior Management Team, investigations were undertaken and remedial works actioned to ensure all leaks are repaired. As the production unit is not currently supplying cooked meals, at no point was patient safety put at risk.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size:12.0pt&quot;&gt;&lt;o:p&gt;&lt;/o:p&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
